node.text:
The Alpina B7… The B now stands for “BAGGGED” ☠️
.
I’ve wanted to see this thing absolutely slammed to the ground since the day it came out. Yeah the grille is massive, but of all the large grilled BMW’s, this one is my favorite and fits the vibe of “ultra crazy luxury sedan”.
.
Needed some more offset with the wheels, so I went with the @rotiform BUC-M to keep the multi-spoke style true to Alpina.
.
So let me hear it, what do you guys think of the grille?

node.text:
My heart goes out to everyone affected by Hurricane Ida.
.
This NFT is up for auction on @withfoundation with 50% of all proceeds going directly to @sbpusa, a 501(c)(3) non-profit devoted to rebuilding communities affected by natural disasters.
.
Ida’s 150mph winds tie it as the 5th strongest hurricane to ever hit the mainland, and second strongest to hit Louisiana, only behind Katrina.
.
1 million people, including all of New Orleans, were left without power Sunday night. 18 water systems servicing 255,000 people were completely knocked out.
.
If you want a chance to own one of my NFTs, as well as donate to a good cause, please check the link in my bio. Stay safe ❤️

node.text:
At first, I thought I didn’t like the new @lamborghini Countach, but I realized I just didn’t like the accents. 

The body itself has been modernized beautifully. It has the side vent, the square headlights, the upper rear quarter vents, etc; and they’re all matching of a modern day Lamborghini. The body is much longer than the original, but they’ve been fine tuning their shape for so long that it would be stupid to go backwards on that.

Now here’s where I think it falls short. The taillights are a cop out; they’re straight duplicates of the Sian, and don’t work. The exhaust isn’t right. I think the headlights are fine, but the front is in need of something else to scream “futUre.” Obviously @lamborghini would never throw 3pc wheels on a production car, but I’m not a huge fan of their choice of wheels.

Lastly… there’s NO WING?!???! I understand the original LP400 didn’t have one, but the LP500 is what I think of when I think “Countach.” That’s just my opinion.

Can’t thank @ar.visual_ enough for hooking me up with a 3d model. If you’re not following him, he does some really great work and even did his own version of the Countach.

Oh and of course @toyotires R888R’s because this thing needs the GRIP.

Let me know your thoughts!

node.text:
The Nissan Z. 400hp twin turbo v6; idk about you, but this makes me happy.
.
@nissan kicked it out if the park here. I think there’s room for improvement with the front bumper still, but being a Datsun guy, I honestly love the throwback.
.
Of all the comebacks we’ve had in the past few years (Supra/Corvette/86/etc.), I think this is my favorite.
